{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17536318","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17536318"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T17:05:50+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T17:05:50+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15750"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15750","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15750"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.03,0.01,0.54,0.02,0.39]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8441"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"93223"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8441","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8441"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15750"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"76544"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"28"},{"type":"tags","id":"44"},{"type":"tags","id":"45"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"94"},{"type":"tags","id":"3870"},{"type":"tags","id":"4789"},{"type":"tags","id":"4978"},{"type":"tags","id":"4979"},{"type":"tags","id":"5803"},{"type":"tags","id":"9222"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11639"},{"type":"tags","id":"11641"},{"type":"tags","id":"11691"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20315"},{"type":"contributions","id":"29720"},{"type":"contributions","id":"29721"},{"type":"contributions","id":"29800"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43592"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"93223","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/93223"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 74-year-old man is admitted to the rehabilitation ward following a left below knee amputation two weeks ago for chronic limb ischaemia. He has a medical history of type 2 diabetes mellitus, hypertension, ischaemic heart disease, and prolonged QT interval. He is a current smoker with a 50 pack-year history. His medications include metformin, gliclazide, aspirin, perindopril, and atorvastatin. He currently requires one assist with mobility and support for all personal care.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears uncomfortable. His pulse rate is 78/min, blood pressure 135/85 mmHg, respiratory rate 16/min, SpO2 97% on room air, and temperature 36.7\u00b0C. The surgical site is well-healed with no signs of infection. He has significant postural hypotension with a drop of 25 mmHg on standing.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHe reports severe burning pain and electric shock sensations in his amputated limb, which are interfering with his sleep and rehabilitation exercises. He also reports low mood and anhedonia since the operation. He has requested a referral to a palliative care physician due to his current symptoms and the distress it is causing him.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Regular paracetamol","Ibuprofen","Gabapentin","Oral morphine","Amitriptyline"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis vignette is consistent with phantom limb pain which is a typical neuropathic pain which develops following a limb amputation, and is associated with decreased quality of life, rehabilitation outcomes, and psychological wellbeing. The presence of pre-existing vascular disease and diabetes likely contributed to pre-amputation neuropathic pain, increasing his risk of developing phantom limb pain.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGabapentin\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate first-line treatment for phantom limb pain. Gabapentinoids work by modulating calcium channels and reducing central sensitisation. They have demonstrated efficacy in multiple randomised controlled trials for neuropathic pain syndromes including phantom limb pain. The medication can be titrated gradually to minimise side effects, and also has beneficial effects on sleep and anxiety.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERegular paracetamol\u003C/strong\u003E is ineffective as monotherapy for neuropathic pain. While it may have a role as part of multimodal analgesia, it would not adequately address the underlying neural mechanisms causing phantom limb pain.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIbuprofen\u003C/strong\u003E and other non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs have limited efficacy in neuropathic pain conditions like phantom limb pain. Additionally, in this elderly patient with vascular disease and likely chronic kidney disease (given his diabetes and vascular disease), NSAIDs carry significant risks including worsening renal function, gastrointestinal bleeding, and increased cardiovascular risk.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOral morphine\u003C/strong\u003E and other opioids have limited evidence in phantom limb pain and neuropathic pain generally. They carry significant risks including sedation, constipation, and dependence. This is particularly concerning in an elderly patient who needs to participate in rehabilitation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAmitriptyline\u003C/strong\u003E would typically be considered as an alternative first-line agent for neuropathic pain. However, in this patient, it is contraindicated due to his history of prolonged QT interval and significant postural hypotension. Tricyclic antidepressants can worsen both of these conditions and increase the risk of falls, cardiac arrhythmias, and other adverse events in elderly patients.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA multimodal approach to phantom limb pain is ultimately recommended, combining pharmacological treatments with non-pharmacological approaches such as mirror therapy, graded motor imagery, and psychological support. Mirror therapy works by providing visual feedback that may help reorganise cortical representations of the amputated limb and can be a valuable adjunct once pain is better controlled. Early referral to palliative care services can be beneficial for pain management and addressing psychological distress in patients with advanced peripheral arterial disease.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Phantom limb pain is common after amputation and should be treated with gabapentinoids as first-line therapy.","Pre-existing neuropathic pain increases the risk of phantom limb pain after amputation.","A multimodal approach including pharmacological and non-pharmacological strategies is important in managing phantom limb pain."],"references":["Kwong M, Curtis EE, Mell MW. Underutilization of palliative care for patients with advanced peripheral arterial disease. Annals of Vascular Surgery. 2021 Oct 1;76:211-7. Available online at ; https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S089050962100488X","Erlenwein J, Diers M, Ernst J, Schulz F, Petzke F. Clinical updates on phantom limb pain. Pain reports. 2021 Apr 1;6(1):e888. Available online at ; https://journals.lww.com/painrpts/fulltext/2021/01000/clinical_updates_on_phantom_limb_pain.7.aspx"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"76544"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15750"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"76544","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/76544"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-20T21:46:08+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-20T21:47:24+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8441"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"93223"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"28","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/